CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 6, 1956, pg. 14, reads: "Controversial Garage - There are still mixed reactions, pro and con, among Schenley Heights residents about the garage-patio which the Haywood McKenzies built at their home at 729 Bryn Mawr Rd. But the construction, which the Allegheny County County Court ruled was built without a building permit, is being dismantled after three years of court battling.  The McKenzies were opposed in their building of the garage by a group led by Mrs. Andrew Brookins, a neighbor, of 727 Bryn Mawr Rd. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Brick house of Haywood McKenzie with partially dismantled garage, 729 Bryn Mawr Road, Shenley Heights
